As many as five men have been killed and a sixth wounded during a shootout with police officers near Pinetown on Monday. It is understood that the men‚ suspected to be responsible for a series of house robberies‚ were tracked by police on the M13 Fields Hill as they travelled toward the city. A dramatic exchange of fire ensued and the vehicle the men were travelling in left the road and overturned. A seriously injured man was treated by paramedics at the scene. This is a developing story.